  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6601.61 sitting just below the massive +49.2B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that level while the PIN regime keeps them buying dips toward the -29.3B gamma pit at 6590. The 490% 5-minute GEX surge and recent wall break signal violent dealer rebalancing is occurring, creating whipsaw conditions as flows amplify moves below 6590 but cap rallies above 6605. Key battle zone is 6590-6605 corridor with the 6612 flip strike acting as the regime pivot—any sustained break above flips dealers to short gamma and removes the stabilizing bid.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect violent chop between 6590-6605 with strong rejection at either extreme.",
